  "response": "One of the most tragic train accidents in history is the **1981 Bihar train disaster** in India, which is considered the deadliest rail accident ever recorded. On June 6, 1981, a passenger train derailed and plunged into the Bagmati River in the state of Bihar. The exact number of casualties remains unclear, but estimates suggest that between 500 and 800 people lost their lives, with many more injured. The accident was attributed to a combination of severe weather conditions, flooding, and poor maintenance of the railway tracks.\n\nAnother highly tragic train accident is the **2004 Sri Lanka tsunami rail disaster**, which occurred on December 26, 2004. A passenger train, known as the **Queen of the Sea**, was struck by the Indian Ocean tsunami near the village of Peraliya. The train was carrying over 1,500 passengers, and nearly all of them perished when the tsunami waves swept the train off the tracks. This disaster is considered one of the deadliest rail accidents in modern history.\n\nBoth of these events stand out due to the immense loss of life and the devastating circumstances surrounding them.",
